config BR2_PACKAGE_SEED_ENTROPY
	bool "seed-entropy"
	help
	  Tiny C binary that credits saved entropy to the kernel random pool
	  using the RNDADDENTROPY ioctl. This makes SSH available immediately
	  on boot instead of waiting ~200 seconds for hardware entropy.

	  Unlike a Python implementation, this binary does not read from
	  /dev/urandom during startup, avoiding the entropy drain that
	  Python's hash randomization causes.

	  https://d-central.tech/
